<h3>Step 4. Create your ebook: end material</h3>
<p>Your work as an author isn&amp;rsquo;t over just because your book has been published. You will need to promote your work vigilantly! first, make sure you have a website for your book. Second, you will want to tap into social media to help you promote your book - don&amp;rsquo;t overlook the power of promotion on facebook and twitter. Third, host book signings and promote your author event using booktour. Com. Finally, create promotional materials with your book cover - postcards, fliers, business cards, letterhead&amp;hellip;get creative here!</p>
<p>while we have seen all sorts of different book cover options over the years. We know from our vast experience, what makes a great looking cover, and what does not. You want a cover to look vibrant, crisp, and catch the potential reader&amp;rsquo;s eye. Investigate your book cover options , and find out what makes a great printed cover. We will also inform you what cover services and finishes to avoid when choosing a printer.</p>
<p>Simon &amp; schuster simon &amp; schuster is a publishing house in the us. It is a subsidiary of cbs corporation. The publishing company came into being in new york city in the year 1924. Richard simon &amp; max schuster are the core founders of the publishing house. So far, simon &amp; schuster has published more than 2,000 titles under thirty-five unique imprints. Simon &amp; schuster has published books for an extensive list of authors. Some of the notable authors are dan brown, ernest hemingway, f. Scott fitzgerald, stephen king, and walter isaacson among others.</p>
